                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="475077" author="tappro" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2025 19:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is not possible to use nodemap info to get client networks for filtering. The only source of information can be request itself, e.g. rq_source. The list of further research in this area:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;check if rq_source contains real client NID in router setup too&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;get LNet peer by rq_source&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;get all list of all peer NIDs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;consider all NIDs attached to peer as client NIDs and use them to build networks list for filtering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;by this we might get possible networks on client though I am afraid with not 100% confidence (do we need it at all?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
